You can create an update set to group the customizations that you want to move from one instance to another.

  • To create an update set:
    1. Enter a name for the update set.
    2. Enter a description for the update set.
    3. Choose from one of the following:
    4. Click Submit to create the update set.
      To create the update set and enable the new customizations to be recorded in the new update set, click Submit and Make Current.
  • To modify details of an update set:
    1. Edit the form fields as required.
    2. Click Update.
  • To set an update set as the current set:
    1. Click the Make This My Current Set related link.
  • To mark an update set as complete:
    1. In the State field, select Complete.
    2. Click Update.

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_8488_ssn_rest.importUtils</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>importUtils</name><script><![CDATA[var importUtils = Class.create();
importUtils.prototype = {
	initialize: function() {
	},

	postUser: function(j) {
		gs.debug('Script Include importUtils postUser has been called');

		try {
			var answer = {}; // Prepare response payload. We will write success/error messages here later
			var importSetRowUser = 'x_8488_ssn_rest_import_user';
			var importSetRowMultiLoc = 'x_8488_ssn_rest_impor_multiple_locations';

			gs.debug('Script Include received payload: ' + JSON.stringify(j)); // Lets just take a quick look at the data

			// I like to setup the node names in advance, easier to change in the future if needed
			var nA = 'sourceA';
			var nAProfile = 'profile';
			var nB = 'sourceB';
			var nBLoc = 'locations';


			//  -- Check Validity of JSON Content before proceding --
			//  Looking for Employee ID in the nodes

			// No Usable Data sets
			if (j[nA] == undefined && j[nB] == undefined) {
				answer.http_status = "400";
				answer.status_message = 'Request Rejected: We expected to see nodes for ' + nA + ' or ' + nB + ' but those were not found. Please confirm before resending';
				gs.error(JSON.stringify(answer));
				return answer;
			}

			if (j[nA] != undefined && (j[nA].employeeNum == undefined || j[nA].employeeNum == '')) {
				answer.http_status = "400";
				answer.status_message = 'Request Rejected: Received node ' + nA + ' but did not find a valid employee number. Please confirm before resending';
				gs.error(JSON.stringify(answer));
				return answer;
			}
			
			if (j[nB] != undefined && (j[nB].empID == undefined || j[nB].empID == '')) {
				answer.http_status = "400";
				answer.status_message = 'Request Rejected: Received node ' + nB + ' but did not find a valid employee number. Please confirm before resending';
				gs.error(JSON.stringify(answer));
				return answer;
			}


			gs.debug('Script Include importUtils is creating GlideRecord to insert onto user Import Set Row');


			// ----------------------------
			// Prepare new records on import set row tables to receive and process customer profile
			// ----------------------------

			var userIn = new GlideRecord(importSetRowUser);
			userIn.initialize();


			// Prefer SourceA
			if(j[nA] != undefined){
				userIn.unique_identifier = j[nA].employeeNum;
				userIn.first_name = j[nA].firstName; // Will be later overwritten if Source B is provided
				userIn.location = j[nA].location;

				// Checking to make sure node and name value pair are present
				if(j[nA][nAProfile].jobTitle != undefined){
					userIn.title = j[nA][nAProfile].jobTitle;
				}
			}

			// Prefer SourceB - Overriding and taking needed fields
			if(j[nB] != undefined){
				userIn.first_name = j[nB].f_name;
			}

			// Use Case: Source A not provided. Use Source B to populate what Source A was expected to populate.
			if(j[nA] == undefined && j[nB] != undefined) {
				userIn.unique_identifier = j[nB].empID;
			}


			// Send the Profile Data to the User Import Set Row Table
			var resultSysID = userIn.insert();

			// Source B is provided, let's send its supplimental data to another import set row table
			if(j[nB] != undefined){
				// Populate the Multi-location table now
			}

			gs.debug('Completing Customer Profile import for ' + userIn.unique_identifier + '. Time to start the multilocation import.');


			// Now we lookup the record that was just created moments ago so we can check how the Transform Map went.
			var importSetRow = new GlideRecord(importSetRowUser);
			importSetRow.get(resultSysID);

			// We will look to see what happened during transform and write the state of the import down
			var importSetRowStatus = importSetRow.sys_import_state;

			//  Package up all clear response
			if(importSetRowStatus == 'ignored' || importSetRowStatus == 'ignore'){
				answer.http_status = "200";
				answer.status_message = "User payload accepted and processed. Data provided matched local data set, update was ignored for " + userIn.unique_identifier;
			}

			else if(importSetRowStatus == 'updated'){
				answer.http_status = "200";
				answer.status_message = "User payload accepted and processed. Account updated for " + userIn.unique_identifier;
			}

			else if(importSetRowStatus == 'inserted'){
				answer.http_status = "201";
				answer.status_message = "User payload accepted and processed. Profile created for " + userIn.unique_identifier;

			} else {
				var msg = 'Unexpected import result during user transform: ' + importSetRow.sys_import_state.toString() + ' ' + importSetRow.sys_row_error.error_message.toString() + ' and error code is ' + importSetRow.sys_row_error.error_code.toString() + ' UserId of user ' + importSetRow.unique_identifier;
				answer.http_status = "500";
				answer.status_message = msg;

			}

			gs.debug('Script Include completing with: ' + JSON.stringify(answer));
			return answer;

		}
		catch(ex) {
			answer.http_status = '500';
			answer.status_message = 'Internal ServiceNow Error: ' + ex;
			gs.error(JSON.stringify(answer));
			return answer;
		}
	},
